records.addlTxt:
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.

Court STAYED the sentence, and placed the defendant on 30 MONTHS probation.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION and EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Restitution was order at $0.00;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*Mental heath assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take all medications as prescribed, only in the manner prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Participate in any treatment that is deemed appropriate by the agent;
*Complete a cognitive thinking program;
*Provide a DNA sample, if not already provided.  If the same has already been provided, the Court will waive the DNA surcharge;
*Court ordered the defendant to serve 8 MONTHS condition time in the House of Corrections, consecutive to any other sentence. No good time credit. Court is opposed to electronic monitoring. During the first half of the condition time, the Court will allow for release to the Day Reporting Center for programming and treatment.  During the last half of the condition time, the Court will also allow release for work.
* Fine in the amount of $600.00, cash bail on deposit to apply;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs, cash bail on deposit to apply; 
If revoked, the Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.


Court ordered Intoxicated Driver Assessment; form filed; copy to defendant.

Court ordered defendant's operating privileges revoked for 24 MONTHS with the mandatory reinstatement fee.  

Defendant's operating privilege for operation of Class D vehicles is restricted to operating vehicles that are equipped with an ignition interlock device; and each motor vehicle for which the defendant's name appears on the vehicle's certificate of title or registration must be equipped with an ignition interlock device beginning on the date the department issues any license and for a period of  24 MONTHS  thereafter.


Appeal rights given. Defendant informed of right as they related to voting and firearms.

Filed;
-Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
